      "avalancheActivity": {
        "comment": "They have received widespread snowfall of 30 to 60 cm of fresh snow, accompanied by strong winds. At higher elevations, the amounts of fresh snow are greater. <br/> The avalanche prone locations are numerous. As a consequence of new snow and wind, deep wind slabs formed. Natural avalanches are further possible. In the regions exposed to heavier precipitation they can in isolated cases reach very large size and in some places endanger transportation routes situated at relatively high altitudes. <br/> Without question, it is inadvisable to engage in backcountry touring.",
        "highlights": "High avalanche danger will persist."
